text: Hawkesbury is an electoral district of New South Wales. It was created in 1859, abolished in 1920 and recreated in 1927. It is a conservative electorate in the Hawkesbury region of New South Wales. Hawkesbury contains a variety of places, including the far northern outskirts of Sydney, a small part of the Central Coast, and some rural towns. ==Election results== ==References== Hawkesbury
